hopobject.body: I'd like to speak to someone about a mortgage fludan.com review When it comes time to hit the campaign trail, there's no better person to take style cues from than Michelle Obama. Huma Abedin, wife of New York City mayoral candidate Anthony Weiner, took a page from the First Lady's book as she appeared by her husband's side in Harlem wearing a bright and breezy red and white checkered dress on July 14, 2013. It was the same look Mrs. O donned during a campaign stop in Dubuque, Iowa on Aug. 15, 2012.
